summary: The document is a forensic analysis report from ABC Forensic Services Laboratory regarding latent print examination and comparison for case B2022-16584. Several items were processed, and latent prints were found on some items but not others. A latent print on a metal box was identified as belonging to Ryan Gillespie, while other prints were insufficient for comparison.
conclusion: A latent fingerprint on a metal box was identified as belonging to Ryan Gillespie, while other prints were insufficient for comparison.

description: Black metal box with latch, containing insulated material and cardboard
Latent print of value found on cardboard, identified as Ryan Gillespie's right thumb
Black Glock 17 pistol, 9x19 mm caliber, with obliterated serial number and unloaded magazine
Latent impressions found but insufficient for comparison
Seven stray 9mm unfired cartridges with Luger headstamp
Known fingerprint standards of Gerald Gillespie
